      <back>
         <div type="commentary">
            <p>The name Ιδαβα, presumably feminine, is not attested, although the similar Ιδας is. The tree of life (which appears in the last line of this inscription), a Jewish symbol in origin, was commonly borrowed by Christians and thus its presence does not decisively indicate religion. Dimensions refer to entire remainder of stone.</p>
         </div>
